<h1>Chocolate Spinach Muffins</h1>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>2 cups baby spinach</li>
<li>1 cup whole-milk plain yogurt</li>
<li>2 large eggs</li>
<li>1/3 cup maple syrup</li>
<li>1/4 cup vegetable oil</li>
<li>2 teaspoons vanilla extract</li>
<li>1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour</li>
<li>1/4 cup cocoa powder</li>
<li>1 teaspoon baking powder</li>
<li>1/2 teaspoon baking soda</li>
<li>1/4 teaspoon salt</li>
</ul>
<h2>Steps</h2>
<ol>
<li>Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F. Grease a standard muffin pan with nonstick spray.</li>
<li>Add spinach, yogurt, maple syrup, eggs, oil, and vanilla to a blender. Blend until very smooth.</li>
<li>In a medium bowl, stir together flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.</li>
<li>Add the blended spinach mixture to the dry ingredients.</li>
<li>Gently stir or whisk until combined.</li>
<li>Divide batter among the muffin cups, using a heaping 1/4 cup per muffin.</li>
<li>Bake for 14â€“16 minutes, until edges are lightly golden and a tester comes out clean. Cool on a wire rack.</li>
</ol>
